text: Wu Hsiao-li (, born 11 October 1983) is retired Taiwanese volleyball player who plays as the main setter in the Chinese Taipei women's national volleyball team. Wu began to play volleyball at the age of 10. She started as an attacker, and soon her position changed to the setter due to her lack of height. == Clubs == * Da-Cheng Elementary School, Taoyuan County (now in Taoyuan City) * Da Liao Junior High School, Kaohsiung County (now in Kaohsiung City) * Chung Shan (2004-2005) * National Taiwan Normal University ==Awards== ===Individuals=== * 2004 Asian Club Championship "Best Setter" * 2005 Asian Club Championship "Best Setter" ===National team=== * World University Games ** Winner: 2005 ** Runner-up: 2003 ===Clubs=== * 2004 Asian Club Championship - Image:Med 3.png Bronze Medal with Chung Shan * 2005 Asian Club Championship - 16px Runner-Up, with Chung Shan ==References== Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:Taiwanese women's volleyball players Category:Sportspeople from Taoyuan City Category:Volleyball players at the 2002 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in volleyball Category:Volleyball players at the 2006 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2006 Asian Games Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Chinese Taipei
